Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Press dough firmly into greased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake 20 min. or until golden brown. Cool in pan on wire rack. Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk or electric mixer on high speed until well blended. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread cream cheese mixture over crust; top with strawberries. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.